On America Recycles Day, the United States reaffirms its commitment to recycling as a means of conserving natural resources, creating jobs, and protecting the environment. The country has made significant progress in recycling, increasing the rate from 6 percent in 1960 to 32 percent today. Federal agencies are also implementing waste prevention and recycling in their operations. The aim is to decrease waste output, reuse materials, save money, reduce pollution, and conserve natural resources. The Environmental Protection Agency will be making a special announcement at the America Recycles Summit to further these efforts. The article emphasizes the importance of recycling for the environment and the economy.